Motivational Quote 
This project sends a motivational quote via email every Monday. It reads quotes from a text file and uses the smtplib library to send an email through Gmail’s SMTP server.

Features
Sends a motivational quote every Monday.
Reads quotes from a text file.
Uses Gmail’s SMTP server to send emails.
Prerequisites
Python 3.x
Gmail account with “Less secure app access” enabled.
Installation
Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/UniteUniverse/Python-Programs.git
cd Python-Programs/Project\ 24\ Motivational_Quote

Install the required libraries:
pip install -r requirements.txt

Usage
Update the my_email and password variables in the script with your Gmail credentials.
Ensure the quotes.txt file is in the same directory as the script.
Run the script:
python motivational_quote.py

Code Explanation
Importing Libraries: The script imports necessary libraries such as datetime, random, and smtplib.
Reading Quotes: It reads quotes from the quotes.txt file.
Sending Email: If the current day is Monday, it sends an email with a randomly chosen quote.
File Structure
Project 24 Motivational_Quote/
│
├── motivational_quote.py
├── quotes.txt
└── README.md

